Find $gcd(285,255)$.




\[
\begin{split}
\underbrace{285}_{b_0} &= \underbrace{255}_{a_0} \underbrace{1}_{q_0} + \underbrace{30}_{r_0}
\\
\class{steps3 steps}{
\underbrace{255}_{b_1 = a_0}
}
&
\class{steps3 steps}{=\underbrace{30}_{a_1 = r_0} \underbrace{8}_{q_1} + \underbrace{15}_{r_1}}
\\
\class{steps3 steps}{\underbrace{30}_{b_2}} 
&
\class{steps3 steps}{=\underbrace{15}_{a_2} \underbrace{2}_{q_2} + \underbrace{0}_{r_2}}
\end{split}
\]


So, $gcd(285, 255) = r_1 = 15$.
